OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1772016033
OL,3,CPoliticians in Wales vote to approve
OL,4,Cassisted dying services on Welsh NHS
OL,6,FThe Senedd vote won't make any
OL,7,Fdifference to whether or not assisted
OL,8,Fdying is legalised. Powers to change
OL,9,Fthe law related to suicide are not
OL,10,Fdevolved to Cardiff, so should the UK
OL,11,FParliament legislation pass, it will
OL,12,Fbecome legal in both Wales and England.
OL,14,FBut there are a lot of issues yet to
OL,15,Fbe resolved in Westminster. The
OL,16,FTerminally Ill Adults (End of Life)
OL,17,FBill is currently in the House of
OL,18,FLords, where supporters have raised
OL,19,Fconcerns that the high volume of
OL,20,Famendments could mean the legislation
OL,21,Fdoes not pass.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/6
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
