FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1772016033
OL,3,CPoliticians in Wales vote to approve
OL,4,Cassisted dying services on Welsh NHS
OL,6,FIf the Senedd voted to reject, the UK
OL,7,FParliament could decide to ignore the
OL,8,FSenedd vote, but the backers of the
OL,9,Flegislation have said they would
OL,10,Fchange the bill to redact parts
OL,11,Frelating to Wales if MSs voted against
OL,12,Fit.
OL,14,FIf the Senedd had refused to give
OL,15,Fconsent to the England and Wales bill,
OL,16,Fit could have meant that services are
OL,17,Fstill available in Wales but not on
OL,18,Fthe NHS.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/6
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1772016033
OL,3,CPoliticians in Wales vote to approve
OL,4,Cassisted dying services on Welsh NHS
OL,6,FThat's because health is devolved, so
OL,7,Fthe implementation of any assisted
OL,8,Fdying service would be carried out
OL,9,Fthrough the Welsh NHS which is
OL,10,Fcontrolled by the Welsh Government and
OL,11,Fultimately answerable to the Senedd
OL,12,Fitself.
OL,14,FA rejection of the service on the NHS
OL,15,Fwould have raised the prospect of
OL,16,Fassisted dying being legalised here in
OL,17,FWales but Welsh doctors being
OL,18,Fprohibited from providing the service
OL,19,Fon the NHS. It wouldn't prevent
OL,20,Fcharities or private sector companies
OL,21,Foffering the service.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/6
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
